data.title: Compose music | ElevenLabs Documentation
data.content:
Compose a song from a prompt or a composition plan.

### Headers

xi-api-keystringRequired

### Query parameters

output\_formatenumOptionalDefaults to `mp3_44100_128`

Output format of the generated audio. Formatted as codec\_sample\_rate\_bitrate. So an mp3 with 22.05kHz sample rate at 32kbs is represented as mp3\_22050\_32. MP3 with 192kbps bitrate requires you to be subscribed to Creator tier or above. PCM with 44.1kHz sample rate requires you to be subscribed to Pro tier or above. Note that the Œº-law format (sometimes written mu-law, often approximated as u-law) is commonly used for Twilio audio inputs.

Show 19 enum values

### Request

This endpoint expects an object.

promptstring or nullOptional `<=2000 characters`

A simple text prompt to generate a song from. Cannot be used in conjunction with `composition_plan`.

composition\_planobject or nullOptional

A detailed composition plan to guide music generation. Cannot be used in conjunction with `prompt`.

## Overview

Eleven Music is a Text to Music model that generates studio-grade music with natural language prompts in any style. It‚Äôs designed to understand intent and generate complete, context-aware audio based on your goals. The model understands both natural language and musical terminology, providing you with state-of-the-art features:

- Complete control over genre, style, and structure
- Vocals or just instrumental
- Multilingual, including English, Spanish, German, Japanese and more
- Edit the sound and lyrics of individual sections or the whole song

Created in collaboration with labels, publishers, and artists, Eleven Music is cleared for nearly all commercial uses, from film and television to podcasts and social media videos, and from advertisements to gaming.
